				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Need AA Path Advice<a name="49925"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 3 04 1:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have read the thread about the most useful bard AA's for different situations (melee, pulling, raiding, etc) but I still am a bit confused about what to do next.
<br />

<br />
I raid twice a week and usually I am the only bard on the raid. The remainder of my play time I am usually the puller in LDON, or grouping anywhere usually meleeing and CCing as necessary.
<br />

<br />
My AA path so far:
<br />
Innate Run Speed 1/1/1
<br />
Innate Regen 1/1/1
<br />
Natural Durability 2/4/6
<br />
Fading Memories 6
<br />
Instrument Mastery 3/0/0
<br />
Singing Mastery 3/0/0
<br />
Jam Fest 3/6/0
<br />

<br />
Obviously I cannot go back and correct my past mistakes, for example if I had it to do over I would have gotten CA3 instead of ND3, also with JF1 and JF2 I have not noticed any improvements and wish I had spent those points elsewhere.  Before I make any similar mistakes this is what I have drafted as my AA path from here on out, well the next 150 points or so<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> and would appreciate any advice based on my play style:
<br />

<br />
IM2 - 6
<br />
SM2 - 6
<br />
CA1 - 2
<br />
CA2 - 4
<br />
CA3 - 6
<br />
PE - 5
<br />
MC1 - 2
<br />
CF1 - 2
<br />
LR1 - 3
<br />
LR2 - 3
<br />
IM3 - 9
<br />
LR3 - 3
<br />
LR4 - 3
<br />
LR5 - 3
<br />
SM3 - 9
<br />
MC2 - 4
<br />
CF2 - 4
<br />
MC3 - 6
<br />
CF3 - 6
<br />
PP1 - 2
<br />
JF3 - 9
<br />
PP2 - 2
<br />
IIM - 12
<br />
PP3 - 2
<br />
PP4 - 2
<br />
ISM - 12
<br />
PP5 - 2
<br />

<br />

<br />
My thinking? First get Muse<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Next work on avoidance which I consider to be most important, and then keep on increasing song effectiveness.  Finally, mix some low cost AAs in with the high cost AAs to keep motiviation high, eg MC1 is cheap and since I have only FT1 so far I thought it could help with FM, and CF1 is cheap and I miss notes alot so I would love any help in that area.
<br />

<br />
AA missing from my list but on the recommended list are Extended Notes and Sionachie's Crescendo, I just don't see them being that important compared to others I could be getting, especially if I am off pulling. I am basing this on what I understand is that they only affect my group, and therefore not widely useful in raid situation, please correct me if I am wrong. I don't have CS or ID listed because of what I have read in previous discussions, maybe those are the ones I would do next after finishing this list.
<br />

<br />
I look forward to your advice!
<br />
</span></td>
