				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need AA Path Advice<a name="53776"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 26 04 1:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I feel I am in the same path as you.  I pull..alot, in LDON.  But I also solo alot.  With that said this is what I've done so far and in their proper order:
<br />

<br />
- Run 3
<br />
- Regen 3
<br />
- FM (duh)
<br />
- Natural Durability 1, 2, 3 (HP is good no matter what)
<br />
- Mental Clarity 1, 2
<br />
- Instrument Master 1, 2, 3  (highly recommend all 3 levels)
<br />

<br />
Then I started spreading things out:
<br />
- Combat Agility 2
<br />
- Combat Stability 1
<br />
- Physical Enhancement (more HP)
<br />

<br />
I haven't started singing mastery yet, I think in my situation (same as yours) that mitigating and avoiding damage is the best course.  I notice I take more damage pulling than I should...hence my decisions so far.
<br />

<br />
I'm thinking you should finish out IM, work on the defensive stuff, then start Singing (or anything else).  I've heard too much controversy with Jamfest to work on it until I have other AA's complete.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
