			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need AA Path Advice<a name="54250"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 29 04 10:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Note 1: I do have Lullaby of Morell but have found it to be resisted way too much, this is even with JF2, I swear the song is broken or something and I don't even bother memming it)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Lol, actually I havn't noticed a difference in resists between the two, other than Morell is 10 times better because it doesn't move the mob.  Per lucy the resist checks are the same, would recommend you try it out again.  It could have been when you tried it you where in a hard to mezz dungeon (some are like that).  On JF see below.  
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Since you like to pull LDoNs (not sure if you do hards or not) jam Fest 3 should be a priority, as well as maxing charisma of course. Jam Fest 3 will give you fewer resists which could go critical (charisma to get a lower rate of criticals among the fails). </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
This is unproven and not something you should base anything off of.  You would think it would work like this but no one has ever proved it with extensive testing.  See the concert hall for more info. there is a large discussion on it in the hall of fame part of the board.  I was pulling hards with no problem with mezzing w/o JF and havn't noticed an improvement (on resists, base numbers are better) since I have gotten it. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">IM3 will be nice too, but SM3 is not to be overlooked because our top lull and top mez and PoV are all singing based. I'd work on those...</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Mezz and Lull are not affected by SM.  If there was a resist adjustment to the songs maxing the modifer would help but since there isn't...  Charisma helps with lull and minorly with mezz.  
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Raid Bard should have IM3, SM3, JF3 and EN3. Depending on your instruments, you may want to look into AT as well.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
JF3 will help a bit on adding resists and generally overall, but one of the main reasons most guilds require it is if there is more than one bard and if not everyone has JF at the same level, the songs don't overlap and you begin to have problems with songs dropping when they shouldn't.  You would probably be better off maxing EN/SC first to get the max coverage you can.  
<br />

<br />
As far as other aa's to get first.
<br />

<br />
CF1 than Bellow  -- This is one best aa's that you can get if you are a puller past FM.  Tags become simple, mezz holding a mob and breaking with no time lost is awsome.  
<br />

<br />
LR5 --- &lt;3 it, live it, get it.  Cannot say enough good things about it other than ND is completely overrated when things triple for more than 500.  Was able to pull hards with 3k hps in pickup groups and take a round or two of hits while the tank got aggro.  Also helps with raid pulling and surviving rampage.  I look at it this way.  What good are all those wonderfull instrument aa's if you are dead?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
